LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:coefficients-matrix-format"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

) implies (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:coefficients-inner-products"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 However, the implication from (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:coefficients-inner-products"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

) to (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:the-coefficient-problem"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

) is not as straightforward.
 Assuming (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:coefficients-inner-products"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

